.TH "qib_sd7220_reg_mod" 9 "qib_sd7220_reg_mod" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qib_sd7220_reg_mod \- modify SERDES register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qib_sd7220_reg_mod
.BI "(struct qib_devdata *dd "  ","
.BI "int sdnum "  ","
.BI "u32 loc "  ","
.BI "u32 wd "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dd" 12
the qlogic_ib device
.IP "sdnum" 12
which SERDES to access
.IP "loc" 12
location - channel, element, register, as packed by \fBEPB_LOC\fP macro.
.IP "wd" 12
Write Data - value to set in register
.IP "mask" 12
ones where data should be spliced into reg.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Basic register read/modify/write, with un-needed acesses elided. That is,
a mask of zero will prevent write, while a mask of 0xFF will prevent read.
returns current (presumed, if a write was done) contents of selected
register, or <0 if errors.
